The paper proposes an algorithm for training machine learning models in a risk-averse manner, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm involves stochastic optimization, which is a common technique in data science (cs.DS). The problem is formulated as a zero-sum game, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and the algorithm involves an efficient no-regret algorithm, which is a topic in control theory (cs.SY).
